        Stay away from phoney deals on let's talk.com
    


            by
            ckupsr
                             /
            May 14, 2007 4:59 AM PDT
        

            In reply to:

                            DO NOT BUY PHONE FROM LET'S TALK.COM




I had a similar experience with let's talk.com. I placed an order to add a line to my existing account and convert to a family talk plan for Cingular on 5/3/07. They were offering the Sony Ericsson phone w810i for $229.99 minus an instant rebate of $180.00 and Cingular rebate of $100, totalling -$50.01, i.e. I was offered $50 after all rebates. After placing the order they sent me multiple emails requesting one information and after the other over a few days time. Even after supplying all the information, they still did not process the order, saying that Cingular was requiring a $150 deposit on my order. I have been a customer in good standing with Cingular for several years with no outstanding balance or any late payments. So, I called Cingular and and asked why they are asking for a deposit. I was told that they did not require any deposit from me to add another line. I called Let's talk and told them about my conversation with Cingular. So, then they agreed to proceed with the order after I gave the phone number and name of the Cingular representative I talked to. After a day or two again they emailed me with the same message saying that I need to pay a deposit of $150 that Cingular is asking to process the order. They even quoted some credit reporting agency which did my credit check. I ordered a credit report from the agency and found that Let's talk never ordered any report. My report came out clean as well. I have had a friend who had problem with their order through let's talk too. I called let's talk and cancelled my order. So, deal with this company at your own risk !


