As I said in my earlier post, I thought when I received my phones, all was well.  For some reason Let's Talk said I couldn't keep my two old ATT phone numbers, even though I only wanted to migrate my service over to Cingular.  Although I was on a family plan, they assigned me two new numbers with different area codes.  I contacted them and they changed one of the numbers. When I checked the Cingular website I discovered I now had five phone lines on my account; my original two, the two new ones, and the one with the different area code.  I ended up going to the Cingular store, where they had to wipe out the entire transaction and start the order over. It was a hassle but I ended up being able to keep my original phone numbers after all.


