        Don't be tempted
    


            by
            edieella
                             /
            August 9, 2007 10:58 AM PDT
        

            In reply to:

                                                STAY AS FAR AWAY FROM LETSTALK.COM




I bought 2 Treos from Letstalk.com, but like everyone else I got the zillion emails asking for this or that, but they could not give reasons why they needed the information.  After seeing this posting, I told them I knew their company was a scam, so they sent the phone with no more emails.  Then, of course, they opened a new line for me instead of upgrading my existing line. I know the difference between an upgrade and new line, but nowhere on the website did it say that I would get a new line, AND the website asked what phone number I wanted the plan to go to (totally deceptive). After an hour on the phone with Sprint, I had to send the phone back and get refunded by Sprint.  Sprint told me that third parties get a $20 commission every time they open a new line, so they'll use any sort of deception to get people to sign up.  Sprint was totally cool about the whole thing, but it was a hassle and obviously not worth it, since now I have no new phone.  I'm going to write a letter to Sprint to tell them about the scam, but I'm sure there are a number of companies that do this, and the new accounts they gain are worth the people they piss off.


